<p class="p">The bias was chosen in this research to assess the reconstructing capacity of GCMs to rebuild the precipitation characteristics, so as to test the rationality of using skill score to assess climate models. Specific equations are listed as follows:
 <disp-formula id="FD5-ijerph-15-02491" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">(5)</label>
  <math id="mm5" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mi class="mi">B</mi>
     <mo class="mo">=</mo>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">|</mo>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mfrac class="mfrac">
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mover accent="true" class="mover">
          <mrow class="mrow">
           <msub class="msub">
            <mi class="mi">P</mi>
            <mi class="mi">s</mi>
           </msub>
          </mrow>
          <mo stretchy="true" class="mo">¯</mo>
         </mover>
         <mo class="mo">−</mo>
         <mover accent="true" class="mover">
          <mrow class="mrow">
           <msub class="msub">
            <mi class="mi">P</mi>
            <mi class="mi">o</mi>
           </msub>
          </mrow>
          <mo stretchy="true" class="mo">¯</mo>
         </mover>
        </mrow>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mover accent="true" class="mover">
          <mrow class="mrow">
           <msub class="msub">
            <mi class="mi">P</mi>
            <mi class="mi">o</mi>
           </msub>
          </mrow>
          <mo stretchy="true" class="mo">¯</mo>
         </mover>
        </mrow>
       </mfrac>
      </mrow>
      <mo class="mo">|</mo>
     </mrow>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula> where, 
 <italic class="italic">B</italic> is the absolute value of relative deviation; 
